<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmi:id="-d1D7OhyBLfkuH2-Fzqp2UA" name=",_shASEMhBEd2n-93vLaUXdw" guid="-d1D7OhyBLfkuH2-Fzqp2UA" changeDate="2008-12-12T12:40:52.432+0100">
  <sections xmi:id="_x3KecMhBEd2n-93vLaUXdw" name="Define the type of method/rules to describe policies " guid="_x3KecMhBEd2n-93vLaUXdw">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;P class=MsoNormal style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-US&quot;>&lt;FONT face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;>Decide the strategy that will be followed to describe the policies for the variation points. It will depend on the way to implement the variability of the composition (rules, especial XML documents, etc). Evaluate which is the best option according to the composition engines available and their capacities. &lt;?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = &quot;urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office&quot; />&lt;o:p>&lt;/o:p>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/SPAN>&lt;/P></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_yf2PEMhBEd2n-93vLaUXdw" name="Analyse conditions to launch the alternative selection " guid="_yf2PEMhBEd2n-93vLaUXdw">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;P class=MsoNormal style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-US&quot;>&lt;FONT face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;>The aim is defining the condition to select one of the alternatives or a different one in a formal way. The condition can be more or less complex, but it is common for a variation point, having different valid results (one for each variant).&lt;SPAN style=&quot;mso-spacerun: yes&quot;>&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN>&lt;?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = &quot;urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office&quot; />&lt;o:p>&lt;/o:p>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/SPAN>&lt;/P>&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-US&quot;>&lt;FONT face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;>The information contained in the Variation Points Specification document describes the different alternatives and the conditions in an informal way. Use that information to concretize the condition in a format supported by the mechanisms selected in the previous step or in a format which will allow its translation to the implementation language. &lt;o:p>&lt;/o:p>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/SPAN>&lt;/P>&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-US&quot;>&lt;FONT face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;>Then, specify definitely the context information needed to evaluate all the conditions in the composition. Guarantee that the information will be available at runtime for evaluating the conditions. This might imply including more activities in the workflow (for example, for contacting with a weather forecast services). &lt;o:p>&lt;/o:p>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/SPAN>&lt;/P></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_zo3soMhBEd2n-93vLaUXdw" name="Define the actions to be performed for each variation point " guid="_zo3soMhBEd2n-93vLaUXdw">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;P class=MsoNormal style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-US&quot;>&lt;FONT face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;>Define the actions to be taken when the condition activates an alternative of the variation point. It could be as simple as binding a service, but it would be complex, binding several services and doing various assigns for variables.&lt;SPAN style=&quot;mso-spacerun: yes&quot;>&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN>&lt;?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = &quot;urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office&quot; />&lt;o:p>&lt;/o:p>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/SPAN>&lt;/P>&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-US&quot;>&lt;FONT face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;>Analyse the variants defined for each variation point and the possible actions to be performed in a variant according to its description and requirements. It may be seen as an activity diagram with the flow of activities to be followed when a variant is selected. &lt;o:p>&lt;/o:p>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/SPAN>&lt;/P>&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-US&quot;>&lt;FONT face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;>Have in mind that non functional requirements of the overall composition may be affected by the actions to be performed in the variants, so developers should guarantee that the implementation of those actions will be compatible with the rest of the composition and that they fulfil all the requirements (functional as well as non functional). &lt;o:p>&lt;/o:p>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/SPAN>&lt;/P></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_09XaYMhBEd2n-93vLaUXdw" name="Implement the mechanism for policies execution" guid="_09XaYMhBEd2n-93vLaUXdw">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;P class=MsoNormal style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-US&quot;>&lt;FONT face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;>Translate the design of the policies to an implementation language or specification, according to the selection made in the first step of this task. The execution engine will use the policies to execute the dynamic part of the composition. &lt;?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = &quot;urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office&quot; />&lt;o:p>&lt;/o:p>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/SPAN>&lt;/P>&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-US&quot;>&lt;FONT face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;>First, implement the conditions, since they are described in a formal way and they will be easier to implement. Moreover, they are the entry point to the variants, so the condition will define the starting point of the implementation of the variants. &lt;o:p>&lt;/o:p>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/SPAN>&lt;/P>&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-US&quot;>&lt;FONT face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;>Finally, implement the actions to be performed in each variant, according to the structure of the language selected and the implementation of the conditions. &lt;o:p>&lt;/o:p>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/SPAN>&lt;/P></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <purpose>&lt;P class=MsoNormal style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-US&quot;>&lt;FONT face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;>This task is for designing and implementing the policies to be followed at runtime in order to select the variant to be executed. This means to describe a set of rules or requirements to guide in the selection of services in a variation point according to the conditions defined and the context information gathered. The execution engine will use these policies to give dynamicity to the composition at runtime. &lt;?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = &quot;urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office&quot; />&lt;o:p>&lt;/o:p>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/SPAN>&lt;/P></purpose>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription>
